        "subject": "LU-9441 pltrpc: don't wakeup on 1 second intervals",
        "message": "LU-9441 pltrpc: don't wakeup on 1 second intervals\n\nIf there are no requests on the set there is no need\nto wake up every second. The thread is woken up when a\nrequest is added to the set or when the STOP bit is set.\nSo it is sufficient to only wake up when there are requests\non the set to worry about.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5966c5298c26f8b65a7c212715dc18d889a1a354\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
